---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Layout title="Physics — Simple Nature" favicon="⚛">
  <main>

    <a href="/reading/" class="text-sm mb-4 inline-block">&larr; back to reading</a>

    <h1>⚛ Physics</h1>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-2">Based on <a href="https://lightandmatter.com/area1sn.html">Benjamin Crowell, Simple Nature</a>, licensed <a href="https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/">CC BY-SA 3.0</a>.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-400 mb-6">Calculus-based physics from conservation laws to quantum mechanics. Runnable code, inline diagrams, plain English.</p>

    <!-- SVG: Ball on parabolic trajectory with velocity vector -->
    <div class="flex justify-center my-6">
      <svg viewBox="0 0 360 160" class="w-full max-w-sm" style="font-family: ui-monospace, monospace;">
        <!-- Parabolic trajectory -->
        <path d="M 40 130 Q 180 -20 320 130" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-opacity="0.3" stroke-dasharray="5,4"/>
        <!-- Ground -->
        <line x1="30" y1="135" x2="330" y2="135" stroke="#71717a" stroke-width="1" stroke-opacity="0.45"/>
        <!-- Ball at peak-ish position -->
        <circle cx="160" cy="28" r="8" fill="#60a5fa" fill-opacity="0.6"/>
        <!-- Velocity vector (tangent to parabola, pointing right and slightly down) -->
        <line x1="168" y1="28" x2="220" y2="38" stroke="#f59e0b" stroke-width="2" stroke-opacity="0.7"/>
        <polygon points="220,38 212,32 214,42" fill="#f59e0b" fill-opacity="0.7"/>
        <text x="225" y="42" fill="#f59e0b" font-size="12" fill-opacity="0.6" font-style="italic">v</text>
        <!-- Ball at start -->
        <circle cx="40" cy="130" r="5" fill="currentColor" fill-opacity="0.2"/>
        <!-- Ball at end -->
        <circle cx="320" cy="130" r="5" fill="currentColor" fill-opacity="0.2"/>
        <!-- Caption -->
        <text x="180" y="155" text-anchor="middle" fill="currentColor" font-size="10" fill-opacity="0.35">Conservation laws govern the trajectory.</text>
      </svg>
    </div>

    <div class="overflow-x-auto">
      <table class="w-full text-sm">
        <thead>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-700">
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400">Chapter</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 pr-3 text-gray-400">One sentence</th>
            <th class="text-left py-2 text-gray-400"></th>
          </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-01/">1. Conservation of Energy</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Energy is never created or destroyed, only converted between kinetic and potential forms</td>
            <td><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-01/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">⚛</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-02/">2. Conservation of Momentum</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Total momentum of an isolated system is constant, even through collisions</td>
            <td><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-02/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">⚛</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-03/">3. Conservation of Angular Momentum</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Spinning things keep spinning unless a torque acts on them</td>
            <td><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-03/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">⚛</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-04/">4. Thermodynamics</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Entropy always increases, and that arrow of time constrains every engine</td>
            <td><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-04/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">⚛</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-05/">5. Waves</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Waves superpose, interfere, and decompose into Fourier components</td>
            <td><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-05/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">⚛</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-06/">6. Electricity</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Charges create fields, fields do work, and circuits are the plumbing</td>
            <td><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-06/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">⚛</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-07/">7. Magnetism</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Moving charges create magnetic fields; magnetic forces are always perpendicular to velocity</td>
            <td><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-07/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">⚛</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-08/">8. Electromagnetism</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Changing electric fields create magnetic fields and vice versa: Maxwell's equations</td>
            <td><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-08/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">⚛</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-09/">9. Optics</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Light is an electromagnetic wave: reflection, refraction, diffraction</td>
            <td><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-09/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">⚛</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-10/">10. Relativity</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Space and time are one fabric; nothing outruns light</td>
            <td><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-10/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">⚛</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr class="border-b border-zinc-800">
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-11/">11. Quantum Mechanics</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Particles are waves of probability; measurement collapses the wavefunction</td>
            <td><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-11/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">⚛</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td class="py-2 pr-3 text-gray-300"><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-12/">12. The Atom</a></td>
            <td class="pr-3 text-gray-400">Quantum mechanics explains the periodic table, spectral lines, and chemical bonds</td>
            <td><a href="/reading/physics/crowell-12/" class="text-yellow-300 hover:text-yellow-200">⚛</a></td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>


    <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm mt-8">📺 Video lectures: <a href="https://oyc.yale.edu/physics/phys-200">Yale PHYS 200: Fundamentals of Physics (Ramamurti Shankar)</a></p>

    <h3>Neighbors</h3>
    <ul class="neighbors">
      <li><a href="/reading/calculus/">∫ Calculus</a> &mdash; calculus was invented to describe motion and force</li>
      <li><a href="/reading/linear-algebra/">📐 Linear Algebra</a> &mdash; quantum mechanics and electromagnetism use vectors and matrices</li>
      <li><a href="/reading/information-theory/">📡 Information Theory</a> &mdash; thermodynamics and entropy share a deep connection</li>
    </ul>

  </main>
</Layout>
